Painting still lives in warm, cold and neutral colors. Presenting shapes by light and shades. Analysis of light and shade on the basis of still life in similar light shades. Color circle, different types of harmony, contrasting colors.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Developing a sense of creating a whole by the ability to see colors and convey them through the means of painting, by the ability show shapes and intensity. Acquiring the basic principles of the theory of colorsLearning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon successful completion of the course students: -	can see and understand the color qualities, shades, lightness and darkness, saturation, air perspective, and relationships between light and shade in the surrounding environment and items. -	know and use the principles of creating the scenic whole by the help of color scheme proceeding from the needs of the specialty -	know important principles of color studies necessary for painting and applies them creatively -	can motivate themselves for creative work -	can analyze and evaluate their working process and its outcome
